le-sclerosis</guid></item><item><title>痴呆症的自动成像区分，包括阿尔茨海默病痴呆和路易体痴呆</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/automated-imaging-differentiation-for-dementiaincluding-alzheimer-disease-dementia-and-dementia-with-lewy-bodies</link><description>老年人痴呆的两个最常见原因是阿尔茨海默病痴呆（ADD）和路易体痴呆（DLB）。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/automated-imaging-differentiation-for-dementiaincluding-alzheimer-disease-dementia-and-dementia-with-lewy-bodies.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 00:39:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/automated-imaging-differentiation-for-dementiaincluding-alzheimer-disease-dementia-and-dementia-with-lewy-bodies</guid></item><item><title>脂肪细胞通过新发现的神经回路引导苍蝇远离受病原体污染的食物</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/fat-cells-steer-flies-away-from-pathogen-tainted-food-through-a-newly-revealed-neural-circuit</link><description>如果人类或动物吃了一些导致他们感觉不适的东西，他们就会避开这种食物来源。到目前为止，人们还不清楚这种回避学习是如何发生的。一项新的研究表明，脑细胞和脂肪细胞之间的交流可能在这里发挥至关重要的作用。来自波恩大学和东北大学（日本）以及波恩大学医院的参与者揭示了果蝇中以前未知的机制。它也可能以类似的形式存在于哺乳动物甚至人类中。现在结果已经&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/fat-cells-steer-flies-away-from-pathogen-tainted-food-through-a-newly-revealed-neural-circuit.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 00:24:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/fat-cells-steer-flies-away-from-pathogen-tainted-food-through-a-newly-revealed-neural-circuit</guid></item><item><title>噬菌体疗法在抗生素耐药性方面获得动力</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/phage-therapy-gains-momentum-in-antibiotic-resistance</link><description>随着抗菌药物耐药性继续挑战传统治疗方案，噬菌体疗法正在成为一种可行的精准医学替代方案。最近的临床发展表明，这些基于病毒的干预措施有可能针对多重耐药病原体，同时保留宿主微生物组。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/phage-therapy-gains-momentum-in-antibiotic-resistance.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Fri, 17 Apr 2026 00:09:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/phage-therapy-gains-momentum-in-antibiotic-resistance</guid></item><item><title>脂肪产生酶可能会加剧帕金森病的损害</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/fat-producing-enzyme-may-amplify-damage-in-parkinsons-disease</link><description>随着果蝇年龄的增长，它们出现了类似帕金森氏症的症状，包括运动受损和脑细胞丧失，这反映了人类疾病进展的关键方面。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/fat-producing-enzyme-may-amplify-damage-in-parkinsons-disease2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 23:54:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/fat-producing-enzyme-may-amplify-damage-in-parkinsons-disease</guid></item><item><title>更安全的大脑植入物背后的微妙科学</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-subtle-science-behind-safer-brain-implants</link><description>在最近的一份出版物中&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-subtle-science-behind-safer-brain-implants.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 23:39:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/the-subtle-science-behind-safer-brain-implants</guid></item><item><title>可与活脑细胞“对话”的可打印人工神经元</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/printable-artificial-neurons-that-talk-to-living-brain-cells</link><description>人工神经元可以与大脑对话吗？可打印的基于 MoS2 的神经元可触发活体小鼠脑组织的反应。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/printable-artificial-neurons-that-talk-to-living-brain-cells.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 23:24:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/printable-artificial-neurons-that-talk-to-living-brain-cells</guid></item><item><title>宇宙弦——宇宙结构中的裂缝</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/cosmic-strings-cracks-in-the-fabric-of-the-universe</link><description>&lt;img src="https://politepol.com/fd/NjxHZtldG2if.xml" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Thu, 16 Apr 2026 23:09:06 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/04/cosmic-strings-cracks-in-the-fabric-of-the-universe</guid></item></channel></rss